  "response": "I'll help you with guess estimate questions. These are typically questions that ask you to make a reasonable estimate or educated guess about a quantity without using precise calculations. Here are some tips and example approaches:\n\nTips for Guess Estimates:\n1. Break down complex problems\n2. Use known references or benchmarks\n3. Make logical assumptions\n4. Round numbers for easier calculation\n5. Show your reasoning\n\nExample Questions and Approaches:\n\n1. How many golf balls could fit in a school bus?\n\u2022 Estimate bus volume\n\u2022 Estimate golf ball size\n\u2022 Divide bus volume by golf ball volume\n\n2. How many paperclips could stack from ground to ceiling?\n\u2022 Measure paperclip height\n\u2022 Measure room height\n\u2022 Divide room height by paperclip height\n\n3. How many pizzas are eaten in your city daily?\n\u2022 Estimate population\n\u2022 Guess percentage who eat pizza\n\u2022 Average pizzas per person\n\n4. How many ping pong balls fit in a Boeing 747?\n\u2022 Estimate plane interior volume\n\u2022 Estimate ping pong ball volume\n\u2022 Do simple division\n\nWould you like me to walk through a specific guess estimate problem in detail?",
